==English==
===Etymology===
''[[hide]]'' + ''[[-eth]]'', the archaic third-person singular present tense suffix

===Verb form===
'''hideth'''
# {{archaic}} [[third-person singular]] form of ''to [[hide]]''.
#:{{RQ:Authorized Version}} [[Matthew]] 13:44, ''Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto treasure hid in a field; the which when a man hath found, he hideth, and for joy thereof goeth and selleth all that he hath, and buyeth that field.''